Blurb::
Define abscissa values for the probability density function of each histogram variable
Description::

\c abscissas is required when using \c histogram_bin_uncertain variables.
It defines abscissa values ("x" coordinates) for the probability density 
function of each histogram variable. The \c abscissas keyword accepts a list 
of values. See  \ref variables-histogram_bin_uncertain for details. 

